    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\noxlint's cmd function\n```lua\n  cmd = function(dispatchers, config)\n    local cmd = 'oxlint'\n    if (config or {}).root_dir then\n      local local_cmd = vim.fs.joinpath(config.root_dir, 'node_modules/.bin', cmd)\n      if vim.fn.executable(local_cmd) == 1 then\n        cmd = local_cmd\n      end\n    end\n    return vim.lsp.rpc.start({ cmd, '--lsp' }, dispatchers)\n  end,\n```\ndoes not check for if nvim is running under win32, and tries to spawn using the bash version instead.\nHere's the error code:\n```\n...s64/ucrt64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_transport.lua:68: Spawning language server with cmd: `{ \"C:/path/to/some/projects/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\", \"--lsp\" }` failed. The language server is either not installed, missing from PATH, or not executable.\n```\nI'm using the default configurations from nvim-lspconfig, only capabilities and on_init functions have been modified.\n\nThis fix has worked for me so far\n```lua\n  cmd = function(dispatchers, config)\n    local cmd = 'oxlint'\n    if (config or {}).root_dir then\n      local ext = (vim.fn.has('win32') == 1) and '.cmd' or ''\n      local local_cmd = vim.fs.joinpath(config.root_dir, 'node_modules/.bin', cmd .. ext)\n      if vim.fn.executable(local_cmd) == 1 then\n        cmd = local_cmd\n      end\n    end\n    return vim.lsp.rpc.start({ cmd, '--lsp' }, dispatchers)\n  end,\n```\n\nI'm using nvim 0.12.1",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
